#: src/platform_support.md:1
msgid "Platform Support"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:3
msgid ""
"Being built on cargo and rustc, maturin is limited by [rust's platform "
"support](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/rustc/platform-support.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:5
msgid "Automated tests"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:7
msgid ""
"On GitHub actions, windows, macOS and linux are tested, all on 64-bit x86. "
"FreeBSD is also tested though Cirrus CI, but might get removed at some "
"point. Since CI is very time intensive to maintain, I'd like to stick to "
"GitHub action and these three platforms."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:12
msgid "Releases"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:14
msgid "The following targets are built into wheels and downloadable binaries:"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:16
msgid "Windows: 32-bit and 64-bit x86 as well as arm64"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:17
msgid ""
"Linux: x86, x86_64, armv7, aarch64 and ppc64le (musl), as well as s390x (gnu)"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:18
msgid "macOS: x86_64 and aarch64"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:20
msgid "Other Operating Systems"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:22
msgid ""
"It should be possible to build maturin and for maturin to build wheels on "
"other platforms supported by rust. To add a new os, add it in target.rs and, "
"if it doesn't behave like the other unixes, in `PythonInterpreter::get_tag`. "
"Please also submit the output of `python -m sysconfig` as a file in the "
"`sysconfig` folder. It's ok to edit setup.py to deactivate default features "
"so `pip install` works, but new platforms should not require complex "
"workaround in `compile.rs`."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:28
msgid "Architectures"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:30
msgid ""
"All architectures included in manylinux (aarch64, armv7l, ppc64le, ppc64, "
"i686, x86_64, s390x) are supported. I'm not sure whether it makes sense to "
"allow architectures that aren't even supported by [manylinux](https://github."
"com/pypa/manylinux)."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:34
msgid "Python Support"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:36
msgid ""
"CPython 3.8 to 3.14 are supported and tested on CI, though the entire 3.x "
"series should work. This will be changed as new python versions are released "
"and others have their end of life."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:39
msgid "PyPy 3.8 and later also works, as does GraalPy 23.0 and later."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:41
msgid "Manylinux/Musllinux"
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:43
msgid ""
"`manylinux2014` and  its newer versions as well as `musllinux_1_1` and its "
"newer versions are supported."
msgstr ""

#: src/platform_support.md:46
msgid ""
"Since Rust and the manylinux project drop support for old manylinux/"
"musllinux versions sometimes, after maturin 1.0 manylinux version bumps will "
"be minor versions rather than major versions."
msgstr ""
